  <description type="morphology">Plants 100–200(–300) cm. Stems proximally ribbed (and purplish), distally angular (and greenish). Basal leaves: (petioles with brownish hairs) blades ovate to cordate-ovate, to 10 cm (bases truncate), margins denticulate. Cauline leaves: proximal petiolate, deltate-hastate, margins dentate (faces glabrous); distal petiolate or sessile, smaller (faces finely puberulent). Involucres (7.5–)9–11 mm. Phyllaries lance-ovate, midvein wings uniform or highest at apices. Corollas white or purplish, 8.5–9.5(–10.5) mm. Cypselae fusiform, 3 mm; pappi (6–)7–8 mm. 2n = 50.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering mid May–early Jul (Aug–Sep, peninsular Florida).</description>
  <description type="habitat">Wet or mucky soils, along streams, swamps, woodlands;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0–100 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Ala., Fla., Ga.</description>
